Script,BasicNTResponse
window.currentPBSScenario = 'BasicNTResponse';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Basic_NT_Response';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for BasicNTResponse');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'BasicNTResponse',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1N +Pass +(Pass|2N|3N|4N|6N)
*/
# curate: kind=bidding
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge


dealer north

# Opener — partner (North) holds a standard 1NT: 15-17 HCP, balanced
nShape = shape(north, any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332 - 5xxx - x5xx)
nHcp   = hcp(north) > 14 and hcp(north) < 18
northHand = nShape and nHcp

# Responder — YOU (South): balanced, NO 4-card major (so no Stayman
# temptation), NO 5-card suit (so no transfer temptation). HCP 0-19 so the
# full response table (incl. 6NT = 18+) can occur.
sShape    = shape(south, any 4333 + any 4432) and spades(south) < 4 and hearts(south) < 4
sHcp      = hcp(south) >= 0 and hcp(south) < 20
southHand = sShape and sHcp

eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

northHand and southHand and eHcp and wHcp

action printoneline,
average "Pass-out (south 0-7)   " 100 * (hcp(south) < 8),
average "2NT raise (south 8-9)  " 100 * (hcp(south) > 7 and hcp(south) < 10),
average "3NT (south 10-15)      " 100 * (hcp(south) > 9 and hcp(south) < 16),
average "4NT invite (south 16-17)" 100 * (hcp(south) > 15 and hcp(south) < 18),
average "6NT (south 18-19)      " 100 * (hcp(south) > 17),
`, "N", true)
Script
Button,Basic 1NT Responses,\n\
--- Responding to 1NT — natural responses only (beginner)\n\
Partner (North) opens 1NT (15-17 HCP balanced). YOU (South) respond using\n\
NATURAL responses — no Stayman，no transfers.\n\
\n\
Your responses:\n\
• Pass — 0-7 HCP，balanced\n\
• 2NT — 8-9 HCP balanced，invitational\n\
• 3NT — 10-15 HCP balanced\n\
• 4NT — quantitative slam invite (16-17 HCP，no fit-finding)\n\
• 6NT — slam，18+ HCP\n\
\n\
You are constrained to have NO 4-card major and NO 5-card suit，so the right\n\
answer is always a natural NT raise (or pass). Stayman and transfers don't\n\
apply here. The whole decision is YOURS: read your strength and place the\n\
contract.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/1nt_15_17.php\n\
%BasicNTResponse%
